.TH "Element.clientLeft" "JS" "January 16, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Element.clientLeft \- Element: clientLeft property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The width of the left border of an element in pixels.
It includes the width of the vertical scrollbar if the text direction of
the element is right\-to\-left and if there is an overflow causing a
left vertical scrollbar to be rendered.
\f[CR]clientLeft\f[R] does not include the left margin or the left
padding.
\f[CR]clientLeft\f[R] is read\-only.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This property will round the value to an integer.
If you need a fractional value, use
\f[CR]element.getBoundingClientRect()\f[R].
.RE
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] When an element has \f[CR]display: inline\f[R],
\f[CR]clientLeft\f[R] returns \f[CR]0\f[R] regardless of the
element\[cq]s border.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A number.
.SH EXAMPLES
In the following example, the client area has a white background and a
24px black \f[CR]border\-left\f[R].
The \f[CR]clientLeft\f[R] value is the distance from where the margin
(yellow) area ends and the padding and content areas (white) begin: that
is, 24px.
